    "created_at": "2016-04-21T08:29:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-21T08:31:00Z",
    "body": "Sadly I can't just disable pointer events on the window decoration else users might get confused where else to drag their windows from; and I'm assuming that would affect children as well such as the window control buttons inside that element but thanks for the suggestion.\n\nThis topic does sound rather pedantic but for windows that most certainly should not be maximizable it is pretty tedious.. The reason I haven't just set whether the window can be maximizable for each window with a custom property is because I handle all windows with one channel from IPC:\n\n```\nipc.on('maximize', () => {\n    let focusedWindow = BrowserWindow.getFocusedWindow();\n\n    if (focusedWindow.isMaximized()) {\n        focusedWindow.unmaximize();\n    } else {\n        focusedWindow.maximize();\n    }\n});\n```\n\nAnother solution might be to have the window store an empty object, which you can populate with custom properties? That would be easy to make checks when manipulating a window like this, and plenty of other things.\n"
